parameters:
Clea: This is a town by the sea... This is the smell of the
sea. It's my first time seeing the ocean in my life.

Thief Nora: I smell a scent I've never smelled before. It's
like the scent of a place that is not the empire.

Priestess Sophia: This town serves as a trading hub, so
various people come and go here.

Mage Relm: Sophia-san, you seem to know everything. Did you
perhaps used to travel in the past?

Priestess Sophia: Ahaha, there may have been times like
that~

Guild Leader Agonia: Let's go to the harbor office. I have
already moved ahead to the front of the office.
Clea: Is the client over there?

Guild Leader Agonia: The main target is still ahead, so
let's start by dealing with the entourage first.
Mage Relm: Sigh... I have a bad feeling about this.

Guild Leader Agonia: Well, we have arrived. First, I will
go in, so if it gets noisy, please come.
Thief Nora: Hey, is it going to get noisy!?

Guild Leader Agonia: Yes, this is the office of the illegal
organization that controls this town, so they will likely
resist.

Guild Leader Agonia: Well, let's discuss the details
inside.
Angry Thug: Hey, hey, who the hell are you!?
Arrogant Thug: You think you know where this is, huh!?
Mage Relm: I-Isn't it bad if we don't go help!?
Priestess Sophia: Ahaha, I think I'll be fine.
Thief Nora: W-What should we do, Clea-san?
Clea: Let's prepare first before we go.
Clea: The sound has become intense. Let's go.

Organization Thug: Oh no, who is that old man...! If we
don't call for backup, we'll all be killed!

Organization Thug: W-Who are you guys?! If you're with that
old man, we won't show any mercy!

Clea: That person is our boss. We can't afford to call for
backup.

Great merchant Acreo: Who are you guys? This is not a place
for people like you to come.

Clea: Are you Acreo-sama? We came from the Adventurer's
Guild, Ftera.

Great merchant Acreo: Hmph! What do you want now, you
useless bunch!

Great merchant Acreo: Disappear quickly! I have the backing
of the organization in this town!

Clea: We came to the office to talk to you. Guild Master
Agonia has something to discuss with you.

Great merchant Acreo: Hmph, I do business with the Empire
as well. If you try to harm me, the guards won't stay
silent.

Guild Master Agonia: Clea, Lesson 2 is to block the
opponent's retreat before engaging in negotiations.
Guild Master Agonia: Acreo, you lied to us, didn't you?

Merchant Kinos: Brother... What is going on? Why am I being
framed as an embezzler!?
Great merchant Acreo: W-Well, that is...

Guild Master Agonia: Acreo, who was jealous of your talent,
approached us and requested the murder of the embezzlement
suspect.

Guild Master Agonia: However, the more we investigated, the
more we saw your sincere personality and became suspicious.

Cors the Wanderer: We grew impatient with the stagnant
Adventurer's Guild, so we ordered the assassination of Mr.
Kinos to our organization.

Great merchant Acreo: Huh, but you guys didn't move
either!

Cors the Wanderer: Our big shots must have known that the
Adventurer's Guild was involved.

Merchant Kinos: Brother, turn yourself in. You have done
the worst thing as a merchant.

Merchant Kinos: I have sold my trust and can no longer live
here as a merchant.
Great merchant Acreo: Damn it, damn it!!
Clea: Could it be that they escaped on that ship!?

Guild Master Agonia: Hmm, it seems things have become
troublesome.

Cors the Wanderer: Hehe, what would you say if I told you I
could lend you the Guild Master's ship?

Guild Master Agonia: I'm not particularly eager to owe you
a favor. What are your conditions?

Cors the Wanderer: The condition is to keep the raid on the
office a secret. If rumors spread, it will make our business
more difficult.

Cors the Wanderer: Besides, we were also used and left
behind by Acreo. It's not fair, you know.

Guild Master Agonia: Alright, we won't stop by your office
today.

Cors the Wanderer: You seem to understand the situation.
When you're ready, come to the ship.

Clea: The other party is already at sea. Is it okay to be
so leisurely?

Cors the Wanderer: Ahaha, I'll show you the true power of
the organization.
Cors the Wanderer: Everyone's here, please get on board.

Thief Nora: Wow, this is amazing! It's my first time
getting on a ship!

Mage Relm: How did you all manage to come to this
continent... Did the ship you were on sink or something?
Thief Nora: Um... I can't remember... What was it...?
Priestess Sophia: Are you okay, Nora-chan?

Thief Nora: Um, yes. I'm fine, but I have a lot of vague
memories...

Mage Relm: If you can remember the words, I am an advanced
mage. So please try to remember the words quickly, okay!?
Thief Nora: I-I'll do my best, yes!
Clea: Alright, let's get on board.

Priestess Sophia (Oh my, it's rare to see an age-appropriate
expression from you)

Mage Relm (I wonder if she's really looking forward to the
ship that much. It's a bit childish, so I'm worried.)

Thief Nora: I'm glad Clea-san looks so happy! Come on,
let's hurry and get on the ship!

Cors the Wanderer: Oh man, I got to experience the full
terror of the adventurer's guild, Ftera. It was so scary, so
scary.

Cors the Wanderer: I understand the reason why the
organization doesn't want to get into fights.

Guild Leader Agonia: Thank you for your help this time. If
we have the opportunity to work together again, please take
care of me.

Cors the Wanderer: Please don't ransack the office next
time, okay?

Guild Leader Agonia: I have some business with my younger
brother, Kinos-san, so let's disband here. Well then, let's
meet at the guild.

Cors the Wanderer: Oh man, it was such a scary place. By
the way, ladies, are you interested in doing some work?
Clea: If it's something related to dragons...

Cors the Wanderer: I'm not sure if there are any requests
like that, but if you're interested, you can take a look at
the bulletin board in the office.

Cors the Wanderer: As the renowned Cors the Wanderer, feel
free to ask for my assistance with any requests.
Cors the Wanderer: Well then, excuse me.

Thief Nora: T-Today was such an incredible day, I-I
suddenly feel so tired...

Cleric Sophia: I vomited on the way back, so I feel
nauseous because the alcohol has worn off too much. *burp*

Mage Relm: Honestly, everyone is so hopeless. There might
be hints about dragons on the bulletin board, you know!

Clea (Anyone who violates the three principles, regardless
of internal or external affiliation, will be subject to
extermination... If I were to fight someone from the
Adventurer's Guild)

Mage Relm: What's wrong? Are you spacing out? Look, there
might be hints about dragons!
Clea: Yes, shall we go take a look at the bulletin board?
実績 海辺の冒険者
実績 三傑のやり方
Do you want to enter the office?
Clea (Let's prepare first and then do it)
Clea (I have to go to Acreo's shop)
Thief Nora: He seems like a scary person...

Priestess Sophia: He seems like a typical merchant... It
would be wise to heed Mr. Corus' words, I suppose.

Mage Relm: I wonder where he gets his confidence from...
That arrogance is painful to watch!

Clea: This is a request, let's take care of it
immediately.

General Store Libra: He's being quite persistent... Well,
as for the request, they want to safely pass through the
Mucos Highway.
Thief Nora: Is it safe because that guard is there...?

General Store Libra: Merchants have many enemies, you know!
Are you really an adventurer without knowing such things!?

General Store Libra: Our destination is Fotizona. Please go
straight on the Mucos Highway and don't take any detours.

Pursuer Opis: It's best not to get involved with the
organization, especially Cors. He's the worst person in
Mucos.

Pursuer Opis: You saved me back then, so if you don't mind,
I want you to have this.

Mage Relm: What was that cookbook? It wasn't a grimoire,
just a regular book.

Pursuer Opis: That was a different request's mission order.
Although without a deciphering book, it's just a regular
book.

Pursuer Opis: Thanks to you, I was able to complete the
mission and take back the stolen book from Terra. I intend
to make her pay for it.

Pursuer Opis: Living in Campos will be the final rest for
that swindler.

Mage Relm: What was the reason for being attacked in the
grasslands?

Pursuer Opis: Campos is the territory of the Loparo
Raiders. They must have been displeased that I issued the
request.

Pursuer Opis: Let's stop talking about this. I don't want
to involve you all.

Pursuer Opis: It's best not to get involved with the
organization, especially Cors. He's the worst person in
Mucos.

Organization thug: Thank you for your time.

Priestess Sophia: Are all of you having such a hard time

Thug from the organization: We look forward to your

Prostitute Woman: Oh, a newcomer, huh? You seem like you

Prostitute Woman: Oh, a newcomer, huh? You seem like you

Male Merchant: Take a look at this harbor! It's the symbol

Captain Heeparu: It's another wonderful day for sailing!

Captain Heeparu: Hey, ladies! Are you all drinking

Priestess Sophia: Yes, on sunny days, we drink while
reminiscing about the warmth of the sun, and on rainy days,

Captain Heeparu: That sounds great! Now, let's start with a

Clea: So, what should we do then?

Captain Heeparu: I want you to find my favorite ivory cup.
Since it's also a cleaning operation, you can break anything

Captain Heeparu: Let me know when you're ready to board!
Captain Heeparu: Alright, are you ready to board?
Captain Heeparu: Let me know if you feel like it!
Captain Heeparu: Welcome aboard my ship, the Undutiness!

Captain Heeparu: Ah, this is it! The texture, the shine...

Captain Heeparu: This is the reward and celebration for our

Captain Heeparu: To celebrate the reunion with my friend...

Priestess Sophia: Ahh~ Wine truly is a friend of

events.name: 倉庫の大ネズミ並列（扉）

parameters: Organization thug: 'We're always indebted to our boss.'
Organization thug: 'Ladies, what brings you here today?'

Mage Relm: Being called 'big sister'... it's an unpleasant
sound, isn't it?

Clea: I would like to obtain a Mucos shell. Is it
possible?

Organization thug: Well, it's something to be discarded...
Are you going to use it for magical research or something?

Clea: It seems that it's necessary for the revival of
Valier.
Organization thug: Please give us a moment.
Mage Relm: You seem to be in a hurry, but are you okay?

Organization thug: Sorry to keep you waiting, here is the
shell.
Clea: Is it okay to have this much?
Organization thug: ...It's a gift from the Valier gang.

Organization thug: Valier is a general term for people who
have escaped from Valier and joined the organization. They
have lost hope and fled to Mucos.

Organization thug: It's not out of obligation, but please
convey that I'm happy to hear that there are still people
fighting and that I'm supporting them.
Clea: Understood, I will definitely convey the message.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Organization Thug: 'I would be happy if my hometown could
improve even a little.'
Captain Clevo: Have you sorted out your feelings?

Thief Nora: I still don't understand, but... I still want
to meet and talk.

Captain Clevo: I heard from his subordinates that he has a
favorite place with a great view of the sea.
Organization thug: Leave the guiding to me!

Captain Clevo: I tried to use you like that beastman's
child who tried to sell you.

Captain Clevo: I still haven't forgiven myself, so if
anything happens, please rely on me without hesitation.
Captain Clevo: I will fight for you with my life.

Thief Nora: The captain is stubborn, so it's pointless no
matter what I say! That's why if I'm in real trouble, I'll
definitely go to him for help!

Captain Clevo: It's best if there's nothing, but... please
rely on me without fail.
Thief Nora: I'm fine now, please guide me!
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
Cors the Wanderer: I have a feeling that it's about time.

Cors the Wanderer: I have some circumstances, so is it
alright if we change locations?
Thief Nora: Um... Is it okay if I speak?

Thief Nora: There are still parts where my feelings haven't
settled, but I really want to talk to Cors-san.
Clea: Understood, I'll leave it to you, Nora-san.
Thief Nora: Thank you very much, let's go!
